description: Lucia Nanami, a mermaid princess, has taken human form to find her fellow princesses and save the seven seas from the evil rule of a would-be emperor, the ambitious Gackto. And now Gackto has kidnapped the boy Lucia loves. A final battle is inevitable, but Lucia has found only four of the seven mermaids, and defeating Gackto requires the magic power of all seven!
name: The Villain's Lair!

description: Lucia Nanami and her fellow mermaid princesses have saved the seven seas from Gackto, the madman who tried to rule the oceans with an iron fist. During the battle, Lucia discovered that Kaito, her true love, is actually a prince–and he now knows that Lucia is the mermaid who saved him years ago. But Kaito has vanished during a surfing competition, and Lucia’s dreams are haunted by an ominous angel-like menace. Is there a connection between this new villain and the surprise birth of an Orange mermaid? Lucia must unravel the mysteries. The survival of the human race may depend on her success!
name: A New Mermaid, a New Villain, a New Adventure!

description: Lucia and the five other mermaid princesses have witnessed the rise of a tyrant, Michel, who wishes to transform the world into his twisted image–and it will take more attack power than the princesses possess to stop him! But Kaito, Lucia’s true love, is stuck in a self-made prison of guilt–and the seventh princess has yet to be born. Without the united forces of all seven princesses, and with their allies missing in action, how can Lucia and her friends hope to save the world?
name: A Pitch-Perfect Pitched Battle!

description:
Though the evil deeds of Gackto and Michel are finally at an end, the story fans really want to know still hasn’t been told! Now the wait is over. In the final chapter of Pichi Pichi Pitch, the mystery of Lucia and Kaito’s first meeting is revealed–as well as Lucia’s amazing destiny!

Final Volume
name: The Fabulous Encore

description:
Makoto's doting sister Tsubaki finds out that Makoto hasn't kept his secret from Ito! She threatens to tell Makoto's father unless Makoto and Ito's homeroom can win a school competition.

Then Makoto accompanies the entire Miura household to their ancestral home to meet Ito's eccentric, sharp-witted grandmother. Little does Ito know that her past will catch up with her there - literally!
name: Vol. 6

description: Yoh, Ren, Horohoro, Joco and Lyserg find themselves in their own personal version of Hell. To escape they must reach the level of the five warriors. If they succeed, they will possess the power of the Five High Spirits. But if one of them fails, they will all remain trapped in Hell for eternity!
name: A Good Woman

description: Finally, the shaman slugfest we've all been waiting for: Yoh Asakura vs. Tao Ren! Yoh wants to keep the contest clean, but Ren has other ideas. His crew strikes hard and fast and quickly has Team Yoh on the ropes. Get ready for the biggest Shaman King shocker of them all!
name: The Shaman Fight Shakedown

description: Hao reveals that another tournament has been scheduled to take place on a sunken lost continent far away. This holy land known as Mu is where the Shaman King will ultimately be crowned. Another day... another extraordinary battle for our indefatigable hero!
name: Extraordinary Days

description:
In successive order, Yoh and his crew find themselves pitted against a snake spirit, a spider spirit and an owl spirit. Each freaky adversary presents a puzzle more complex than the one preceding it. And to complicate matters further, Yoh has only fifteen hours to defeat them all.

Chapter Titles

  • Reincarnation 267: Lead's Desert
  • Reincarnation 268: Desert Fillet
  • Reincarnation 269: Manaless Victory
  • Reincarnation 270: Making up
  • Reincarnation 271: A Heavy Door
  • Reincarnation 272: Patch Song
  • Reincarnation 273: Angelic Miracle
  • Reincarnation 274: What a Disgrace
  • Reincarnation 275: Calculating Mana
  • Special Bonus: Funbari Poem: The Bloom of Youth: Mickey's World, Part 2
name: Patch Song

description:
After all these years and all the hard work, Yoh and his gang have finally reached the end of the line. Who will be crowned the next Shaman King, and who will go home in defeat? Get ready for the ultimate pulse-pounding Shaman King battle royale!

Final Volume!

Chapter Titles

  • Reincarnation 276: Announce the Current Values
  • Reincarnation 277: Planetarium
  • Reincarnation 278: Mike Performance
  • Reincarnation 279: Scary Things
  • Reincarnation 280: A Song Someday
  • Reincarnation 281: For Everything
  • Reincarnation 282: Cows
  • Reincarnation 283: For the Time Being
  • Reincarnation 284: Good Night
  • Reincarnation 285: After the Dream

Special Bonus

Funbari Poem: Funbari Hot Springs:

  • Prologue
  • Legendary Warrior
  • Lost Child
  • Trying Hard
  • Funbari Poem
name: A Song Someday

description: Dark Horse Comics brings you the origin of eric Powell's The Goon, te earliest stories published for the first time. The Zombie Priest has just set up hop on Lonely Street and intends to build an undead army, and the Goon's the only man who can stop him. His early battles with the undead are mixed with stories of the Goon's youth, as we meet his circus-feak family and learn how he came to be the head of a notorious crime family. Also included in this volume is a look at the creation of the Goon and his world with a special "Evolution of The Goon" sketchbook section.
name: Rough Stuff
A thrilling picture story reprinted from the Australian Women's Mirror

description:
After orphan Teru Kurebayashi loses her beloved older brother, she finds solace in the messages she exchanges with DAISY, an enigmatic figure who can only be reached through the cell phone her brother left her. Meanwhile, mysterious Tasuku Kurosaki always seems to be around whenever Teru needs help. Could DAISY be a lot closer than Teru thinks?

One day at school, Teru accidentally breaks a window and agrees to pay for it by helping Kurosaki with chores around school. Kurosaki is an impossible taskmaster though, and he also seems to be hiding something important from Teru...
name: Vol. 1

description: When Teru's home gets burglarized, she ends up staying at Kurosaki's apartment. The close quarters lead to tension, but things get even more complicated when a woman named Riko Onizuka shows up, bringing up a past that involves Kurosaki...
name: Vol. 2

description: Teru decides to move out of Kurosaki's apartment, but she wonders if Kurosaki is actually relieved that she's leaving. As she settles in at her new place, trouble comes knocking when an old business acquaintance of her brother's appears...
name: Vol. 3

description:
Ian and Rin used to just see spirits. Now Ian is one. Using the Fairy Cube, Ian must figure out how to stop the lizard-spirit Tokage from taking over his life and destroying any chance he has of resurrection.

Ian is transported to another world by the fairy Ainsel, who promises to help him stop Tokage upon their return to the human plane.
name: Wing 1: Rebirth

description: Tokage has troubles of his own when he gets involved with the Gotoh Group, conspiratorial fairies aiming at world domination.
name: Vol. 2

description: Will Ian save Rin? Can he stop Tokage? Ian has one chance left to get his life back!
name: Vol. 3

description: Rena asks Tomoya to be her boyfriend, hoping that gaining some experience in dating will help her improve her manga. Rena is positive that Tomoya is only dating her to help her out, but that doesn't stop her from falling in love...
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Fall in Love Like a Comic

description: Rena goes on vacation with Tomoya, hoping their trip will be a romantic getaway. She wants to further their relationship, but does Tomoya want the same thing?
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Fall in Love Like a Comic

description: Lucille and the orchestra encounter a town overrun with the worst kind of audience: the living dead! Well, not really. They're people who have been turned into doll-like zombies. And they are definitely not a crowd to take lightly. Can a group of roving musicians use their skills to calm the beasts? Or is this curtains for the Grand Orchestra?!
name: Vol. 1

description: Now that Lucille and the musicians know what they are up against (the zombie-esque Guignols!), they have to figure out how to stop them! Kaori Yuki's new epic adventure offers up not one but two new storylines to savor with "The Queen and the Jester" and the title story, "Tragédie Lyrique." Is the orchestra any closer to stopping the Guignol infestation?
name: Vol. 2

description: Eisen and Little Tengu journey to Funaoka Mountain in search of the second of the Four Sacred Talismans. Unfortunately, they bump into a spirit who insists on blocking their path. One more unyielding phantasm, one more talisman...just another day beyond the stream of time.
name: Vol. 10

description: Working together as the Phoenix of the Heavens and the Phoenix of the Earth, Inori and Shimon go after the Talisman of the South. There are evil spirits hanging around, however, and they need to be vanquished before a third talisman can be added to their cache. Meanwhile, back at Tsuchimikado palace, Akane has an idea about how to stop the ongoing war between humans and demons. Could love be the answer?
name: Vol. 11

description:
Now is the perfect time to get acquainted with the cult-hit that Wizard calls "the most rip-snortin' comics series to hit stands in years,"as Eisner award-winner Eric Powell and Dark Horse Comics present the original The Goon #1 in a new 25 cent edition that includes a brand-new short story and painted cover by none other than the illustrious Mr. Powell himself.

Over the last few years, The Goon has earned both critical and popular acclaim with its tales of a lone thug and his fight against a never-ending onslaught of zombies, giant lizards, and killer robots. For one measly quarter, see why Entertainment Weekly put The Goon on their "Must"list and why Ain't It Cool News said, "The Goon is a wild ride with imaginaion, intrigue, horror, and laughs."You know you want to.
name: Halloween Hoodlums

description:
Meet Casanova Quinn: prodigal son of a law-and-order family hell-bent on keeping the world safe and sound, now blackmailed into betraying his father and the international law enforcement organization he controls. Luxuria collects the first volume of Casanova as its titular star transforms from devil-may-care thrill-seeker into the most dangerous man in the world. What happens when the ultimate player gets played? Find out in this genre-bending sci-spy epic.

Story Titles

  • Execution Days
  • Pretty Little Policeman
  • Mission to Yerba Muerta
  • Detournement
  • Coldheart
  • Women and Men part 1
  • Women and Men part 2

The massive 3-issue miniseries from 1988 is collected for the first time! In this universe- spanning saga, the deadly but emotionless Dominators have come to Earth to wipe out the threat posed by metahumans. But what is the real reason for their attack?
name: TPB
